add looting to implings in hunter

ok so i just thought that hunter was too boring and to easily profitable in [pi] so i decided to write this up the other night so tell me what you guys think

files edited: client.java, playerassistant.java, player.java.
objective: add looting to imp jars.
difficulty: pretty easy
skills needed: simple int knowledge to continue to add looting to all jars 

ok so open client.java and add these int's whereever you plan on adding this, make sure its not in the middle of any public voids or anything like that

[code]int[] DragonImpRare = {/*add your rare reward items here*/}; /*create your list of items and be sure to seperate with commas*/
	public int DragonImpRare() {
			return DragonImpRare[(int) (Math.random() * DragonImpRare.length)];
			}
int[] DragonImpCommon = {/*item ID's*/};
	public int DragonImpCommon() {
			return DragonImpCommon[(int) (Math.random() * DragonImpCommon.length)];
			}
int[] DragonImpBones = {18830};  /*i used frost dragon bones but you can use any bones you want and is even set up to give a random bone if you choose*/
	public int DragonImpBones() {
			return DragonImpBones[(int) (Math.random() * DragonImpBones.length)]; /*finds a random item from the list declared above*/
}[/code]

this is just a list of items telling the server what items to add, and gives it a random item from the list.

now declare this void anywhere in client.java, explains in the code

[code]public void Lootimpjar(int itemId, int playerId) {
if (itemId == 11256){                                                              /*0.01% chance on the first try*/
	if (Misc.random(1000) <= (1 + Misc.random(ImpLuck))) { /*picks a random number out of 1000 if it eaquals 1 + your luck number or less you get a random RARE item*/
		getItems().addItem(DragonImpRare(), 1);
		c.getItems().deleteItem(11256, 1);
		sendMessage("You open the jar and find a <shad=15695415>RARE </col>item");
		ImpLuck = 0;// sets the luck back to 0 when a rare item is earned
	}else{
		if (Misc.random(250) <= (10 + Misc.random(ImpLuck))) {
			getItems().addItem(DragonImpCommon(), 1);
			c.getItems().deleteItem(11256, 1);
			sendMessage("You open the jar and find a <col=1532693>COMMON </col>item");
			ImpLuck -= 2; //takes away 2 luck when a player gets a common item from the jar
		}else{
			getItems().addItem(DragonImpBones(), 1);  calls on the randomizer to pick an item id
			c.getItems().deleteItem(11256, 1); deletes the imp jar from the players inventory
			sendMessage("You open the jar and find some bones");//tells the player what item he got
			//sendMessage("impluck : "+ImpLuck+".");  for testing my luck method
			ImpLuck += 1;// adds luck after each fail
			}
		}
	}
}[/code]	


now go to player.java and add this with the rest of the ints, look for PKpoints thats the easyest way to find them

[code]ImpLuck = 0;[/code]

this sets the int to the server knows what impluck is and what its starts as when u log in, i have it set to be 0 because i want it to reset every time a player logs, add this to the char files if u want it to rollover from each login

then add this in Itemclick2.java

[code]	case 11256:    // dragon impling jar item ID
		c.Lootimpjar(11256, c.playerId); /*tells the server to look in client.java and rune the void lootimpjar()*/
		break;[/code]

this is probly a little sloppy and will be revised to a cleaner method but it works and is reusable for other objectives if needed

